<TEXT>
   A small bomb exploded under a car parked
near a Syrian Army checkpoint in Moslem west Beirut today. Police
said a pedestrian was wounded.
   A police spokesman, who cannot be identified under standing
regulations, said the bomb went off at 8:45 a.m. in the Tarik
Jedideh residential district, about 50 yards from the checkpoint.
