<HEAD>Burglar With AIDS Virus Ordered to Refrain from Sex</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALEXANDRIA, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A judge has ordered a burglar who carries
the AIDS virus to stay home and refrain from sex for five years.
   District Judge Lewis O. Lauve said a report confirmed that
Argentry Eaglin, 21, is a carrier of the virus that causes the
deadly acquired immune deficiency syndrome.
   The sentence Lauve issued Tuesday for breaking probation also
included two years of house arrest under jurisdiction of the Rapides
Parish sheriff.
   House arrest, the judge said, means that Eaglin cannot leave his
home except for employment and other necessary trips.
   In June, Eaglin pleaded guilty to two counts of simple burglary
and was put on probation. He later tried to commit suicide because
he thought he had AIDS, the judge said.
   AIDS has been spread most often through sexual contact.
  
