<HEAD>Infant Shot as He Sits in Babysitter's Car in Drug Area</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 1-year-old boy was shot and wounded in a car
driven by his babysitter through a housing complex while the woman
looked for a drug dealer, Tampa police said.
   Theresa Charlene Robertson, 30, was arrested after telling police
that the infant was shot as she struggled with a man who approached
her car and tried to rob her at gunpoint Tuesday night at the
Riverview Terrace housing complex.
   ``She has admitted to us that she drove over to that area last
night for the sole purpose of buying crack cocaine,'' police
spokesman Steve Cole said Wednesday.
   The infant, Sebastian Placker, was reported in guarded condition
at St. Joseph's Hospital. His mother, Debra Placker, 26, was on a
trip to Philadelphia and left the child with Ms. Robertson, police
said.
   Two other children in the car, Sebastian's 7-year-old brother
Jerome and a 6-month-old child belonging to another woman, were not
hurt, Cole said.
   Ms. Robertson was held on a charge of possessing four grams of
cocaine, the police spokesman said.
