<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ASUNCION, Paraguay (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A state communications company on
Thursday ordered a radio station run by the Roman Catholic Church to
operate at one-tenth power, a move that opposition leaders called
harassment.
   Radio Caritas news director Benjamin Fernandez said the order
from ANTELCO's department of radio communications limits how far the
station can broadcast. It had been reaching most populated areas in
this rural country of 3.5 million, but now is difficult to hear
outside this capital city.
   The station has been one of the most popular and independent in
the country.
