President Gen. Alfredo Stroessner said it was a warning to the
station.
   Radio Caritas was blocked this week from broadcasting a panel
discussion featuring politicians and economists from outside the
governing Colorado Party. Police barred participants from entering
the station.
   Earlier this month, five Radio Caritas reporters were arrested
with opposition leaders organizing a rally for the 40th anniversary
of the United Nations' Universal Declaration of Human Rights. Police
broke up the rally.
   Opposition leaders on Wednesday called 1988 a benchmark year in
their struggle against Stroessner because more Paraguayans openly
opposed his rule.
   The 76-year-old general took power in a 1954 military coup and
has held tight control since then.
