<2ND_LINE>BC-YE--Chronology '88, 2nd Ld-Writethru,1130</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>$adv00</NOTE>
<NOTE>For Release in Year-End Editions</NOTE>
<HEAD>Politics, Tragedy, Triumph: 1988 As It Unfolded</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS Dec. 7 entry to reflect downward revision in official
death toll from earthquake; SUBS Dec. 21 entry to update with bomb
blamed for Pan Am crash and revised death toll. Last update moved
Dec. 22, under same b0962 number.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a chronology of the major events of 1988:
   
   JAN. 2 _ U.S., Canada sign landmark free-trade agreement.
   JAN. 7 _ Record snowfall in the South, record cold across U.S.
   JAN. 28 _ Face-to-face negotiations begin between Contras and
Sandinistas. Polygamist 13-day siege ends in Utah.
   JAN. 30 _ Washington Redskins defeat Denver Broncos 42-10 in
Super Bowl.
   FEB. 3 _ Contra aid voted down by House. Anthony Kennedy
confirmed as Supreme Court justice.
   FEB. 8 _ Dole and Gephardt win Iowa caucuses.
   FEB. 13 _ Winter Olympics open in Calgary.
   FEB. 16 _ Bush and Dukakis win New Hampshire primary.
   FEB. 17 _ Marine Lt. Col. Richard Higgins kidnapped in Lebanon.
   FEB. 21 _ Jimmy Swaggart steps down from pulpit in sex scandal.
   FEB. 23 _ Nationalist protests begin in Soviet Armenia.
   FEB. 25 _ Panama's President Delvalle fails in attempt to fire
armed forces chief Noriega, indicted on drug charges in U.S.
   MARCH 8 _ Super Tuesday: Bush wins 16 of 17 contests, Democratic
results split.
   MARCH 16 _ Poindexter, North, Secord, Hakim indicted on
conspiracy charges in Iran-Contra affair.
   MARCH 23 _ Sandinistas, Contras sign cease-fire agreement.
   MARCH 29 _ Dole drops out of presidential race.
   APRIL 4 _ Arizona Senate convicts, removes Gov. Mecham.
   APRIL 16 _ Khalil al-Wazir, senior PLO commander, assassinated in
Tunisia.
   APRIL 20 _ Two-week Kuwaiti hijacking ends in Algiers.
   APRIL 26 _ Bush clinches Republican nomination with win in
Pennsylvania. In South Korean election, government party loses
legislative majority to opposition groups.
   MAY 3 _ Three French hostages released in Lebanon.
   MAY 4 _ Deadline for illegal aliens in U.S. to apply for amnesty.
   MAY 8 _ Mitterrand re-elected in France.
