<1ST_LINE>r f BC-KodakPrices     12-29 0182</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Kodak Prices,0189</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Kodak to Increase Prices on Range of Products</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eastman Kodak Co. has announced plans for
price increases for nearly all consumer and professional films, as
well as photographic papers and chemicals.
   The increases, announced Thursday, will be effective with orders
beginning January 26, 1989 and are publicized in catalog inserts now
in the mail to dealers.
   ``It's a fairly modest increase,'' said company spokesman Ron
Roberts. ``The increase reflects the general cost of doing business.
It's reasonably normal and not unexpected for January.''
   Roberts said amateur films will increase 3.5 percent, with the
exception of Kodachrome 25 film and Kodachrome 64 film, which will
increase 7 percent.
   The price increases will also affect two camera models: the K40
will increase $3 and the Mickey-Matic will go up $1. Prices on all
Carousel slide projectors are being increased by 4 percent.
   Price increases for professional film will range from 2 to 6
percent. Color papers for photofinishers will rise 3 percent, while
chemical prices will see an average upswing of 3.5 percent,
according to Roberts.
</TEXT>
