<1ST_LINE>u f AM-Dollar-Gold     12-29 0386</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Dollar-Gold,0402</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dollar, Gold Down</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar ended lower against most major
currencies in thin, volatile trading Thursday.
   Gold prices also declined, in what dealers ascribed to yearend
book-squaring. Republic National Bank of New York said gold bullion
was bid at $408.40 a troy ounce as of 4 p.m. EST, down $5.10 from
late Wednesday.
   Dealers said the dollar started out strong with the help of
firmer U.S. interest rates and yearend corporate demand for dollars,
but it retreated after the West German Bundesbank reportedly
intervened to stem the currency's rise.
   Trading, though, was described as extremely thin prior to the New
Year's Day holiday, exaggerating the impact of even the slightest
price movements.
   Little dollar movement was expected on Friday, the last trading
day of the year, dealers said.
   In Tokyo, where trading ends before Europe's business day begins,
the dollar rose 0.76 yen to a closing 126.03. It was quoted at
125.80 yen in London. Later, in New York, it stood at 125.625 yen,
down from 125.68 late Wednesday.
   In London, one British pound cost $1.7900, unchanged from
Wednesday. Sterling fetched $1.7905 in New York, up from $1.7885.
   Other late dollar rates in New York, compared with Wednesday's
rates, included: 1.7875 West German marks, down from 1.7905; 1.5140
Swiss francs, up from 1.5135; 6.0965 French francs, down from
6.1115; 1.19205 Canadian dollars, down from 1.1929; and 1,315.00
Italian lire, down from 1,317.75.
   Late dollar rates in London, compared with Wednesday: 1.7875 West
German marks, down from 1.7960; 1.5125 Swiss francs, down from
1.5177; 6.0975 French francs, down from 6.1225; 2.0190 Dutch
guilders, down from 2.0255; 1.19225 Canadian dollars, down from
1.1963; and 1,314.50 Italian lire, down from 1,320.90.
   On the Commodity Exchange in New York, gold for current delivery
closed at $408.20 a troy ounce, down from $413.90 late Wednesday.
   Gold traded in London at a late bid price of $408.25 an ounce,
down from $413.95 late Wednesday. In Zurich, the late bid price was
$410.75, down from $412.25.
   Earlier, in Hong Kong, gold fell $1.38 to close at a bid $416.07
an ounce.
   Silver prices declined. On New York's Comex, silver closed at
$5.998 a troy ounce, down from $6.088 Wednesday. Silver was quoted
in London at a bid price of $6.04 an ounce, down from Wednesday's
$6.07.
</TEXT>
