<HEAD>Wheeling-Pitt Files Reorganization Plan</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: CORRECTS lede to show plan was submitted in Pittsburgh court</NOTE>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wheeling-Pittsburgh Steel Corp. says it has
submitted its initial plan for reorganization to the U.S. Bankruptcy
Court here.
   A broad outline of the plan, which had been circulated earlier to
the media, said the reorganization would reduce the company's
current common stockholders' ownership to 7 percent.
   Both Wheeling-Pittsburgh and lawyers close to the reorganization,
now nearly four years in progress, said the final plan would likely
look much different than the one submitted Thursday.
   The initial plan is seen as a starting point for negotiations
among the company's creditors, employee groups and stockholders.
</TEXT>
